.SH NAME
polyglot\-deps \- dependency evidence, planning, reporting, and upgrade
flow
.SH PURPOSE
This page explains the dependency\-maintenance helper workflow.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page when you want to inspect dependency state before mutating
the workspace.
.SH PRIMARY COMMANDS
.IP
.EX
task deps:inventory
task deps:plan
task deps:report
task upgrade
task scenarios:verify
.EE
.SH WORKFLOW
The current helper flow is:
.IP "1." 3
\f[CR]deps:inventory\f[R]
.IP "2." 3
\f[CR]deps:plan\f[R]
.IP "3." 3
\f[CR]deps:report\f[R]
.IP "4." 3
\f[CR]upgrade\f[R]
.IP "5." 3
\f[CR]task ci\f[R]
.PP
\f[CR]deps:report\f[R] is the compressed operator\-facing view over the
underlying inventory and plan artifacts.
.PP
The first repo\-owned dependency scenarios build on this flow rather
than replacing it.
.PP
They execute the current Python and Java maintenance patterns and then
verify the expected artifacts.
.SH OUTPUTS / ARTIFACTS
Common files:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-inventory.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-plan.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-report.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]dependency\-report.md\f[R]
.PP
At the repository root, \f[CR]task deps:report\f[R] also produces an
aggregate report over the Python and Java proving paths.
.SH COMMON FAILURES
.IP \(bu 2
Reading only the raw scanner output and ignoring the normalized report.
.IP \(bu 2
Treating \f[CR]upgrade\f[R] as safe without inspecting the plan first.
.IP \(bu 2
